name: Little Kitten My Pet Kitty Cat

editorialNotes.tagline: Holiday fun with a festive feline
editorialNotes.standard: The moment we met wee kitty Crumbs in Little Kitten, we let out an audible awww. This adorable digital feline encourages children to play and explore, interacting with the lively toys and simple games in Crumbs room. Were amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kids screen time is over.
editorialNotes.short: Embark on exciting adventures with your own kitty pal.

editorialNotes.tagline: Play with sun, wind, and air
editorialNotes.standard: Once again, the creators of The Human Body and Simple Machines have turned playtime into a rich learning experience. Tinybops sandbox-style app lets kids experiment to their hearts contentseeing what happens when they move the sun, whip up winds, and cause rainstorms. A zoomed-out view illustrates the broader water cycle at work, while fascinating closeups show things like the effects of changing temperatures and strengthening tornadoes on everyday life. We also dig the detailed study guide offering extra info and discussion ideas.

editorialNotes.short: See internal organs in action: lungs breathe, muscles bend and nerves respond to a pinprick.

editorialNotes.standard: What are those towers that touch the sky? Tinybops awesome sandbox teaches kids the fun wayby letting them build, watch, and play. As they add floors and test the effects of plumbing problems and earthquakes, they're actually learning basic design and engineering principles. Amazing details aboundfrom all the busy little inhabitants to the full-blown skyline you can make.
editorialNotes.short: Learn to build and manage a towering skyscraper.

editorialNotes.tagline: Interact with the power of nature
editorialNotes.standard: Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way thats delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. An accompanying guide for parents and teachers delves into the technical science behind all these phenomena, but kids can explore, experiment, and absorb earthly knowledge at their own pace.
editorialNotes.short: Play with interactive models to understand our planet.

ios.subtitle: Audio to help relax and sleep
Make a routine & put on a show

editorialNotes.standard: Bursting with beats and energy, Toca Dance will make the whole family want to get up and groove. This incredibly cute game puts kids in charge of their own musical productionchoosing dancers, costumes and techno tracks, and choreographing moves using simple swipes and taps. Once the performance starts, the real fun begins: you can fling items at the stage, set off pyrotechnics and other cool effects and even cheer (or boo) your squad. Seeing the payoffan awesome video you can sharewill encourage players to jump right back in and start working on their next great show.

name: Kids Learning to Read - Little Reader CVC Words

editorialNotes.standard: Kids (and kids at heart) can unleash their inner scientists with this captivatingly clever robot-creation kit, which features millions of different combinations for mechanical inventions. Whether youre assembling a wheeled bot with laser guns for arms or a jolly jumping automaton with pogo-stick legs, taking your new bot on a walk through the woods will highlight the successor the rough edgesof your design. While The Robot Factory teaches some nifty physics basics, we like to play around just for the pure fun of it.
editorialNotes.short: Design and experiment with all types of robots.
